    <string name="food_detail_health_info">The amount of health points this food adds to your health bar. Health regenerates at 1%% per second when above 25%% HP. Maximum health is crucial for effective shield use because it directly affects your stagger resistance capacity.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_healing_info">The rate of health regeneration in HP per second while this food effect is active. This healing occurs continuously throughout the food\'s duration.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_stamina_info">The amount of stamina points this food adds to your stamina bar. Stamina is used for running, jumping, attacking, and blocking. Higher stamina allows for longer combat engagements and exploration.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_duration_info">How long this food\'s effects remain active after consumption. The timer begins immediately after eating and cannot be paused or extended.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_eitr_info">The amount of eitr, or magic energy, this food provides. Eitr is required for casting magic spells and using staffs. Only certain foods provide this mystical resource.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_weight_info">The weight of one unit of this food in your inventory. Total weight affects movement speed when you are overencumbered.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_fork_info">The fork icon color indicates this food\'s primary benefit: red for health-focused foods, yellow for stamina-focused foods, blue for eitr-focused foods, and white for balanced foods that provide equal benefits to multiple stats.</string>
    <string name="food_detail_stack_info">The maximum number of this food item that can be stored in one inventory slot. Higher stack sizes save inventory space during long expeditions.</string>
    <string name="mead_detail_duration_info">How long this potion\'s effects remain active after consumption. The timer begins immediately after drinking and cannot be paused or extended.</string>
    <string name="mead_detail_cooldown_info">The cooldown is the time you must wait before consuming another potion or mead of the same type. It prevents immediate reuse and encourages strategic planning in combat or exploration.</string>
    <string name="mead_detail_produced_amount_info">The amount of mead produced by fermenting the mead base for two in-game days.</string>
    <string name="trinket_detail_adrenaline_info">Adrenaline is a personal resource used by trinkets. It is represented by an orange bar in the HUD.\n\nAdrenaline is generated by player actions when the player has a trinket equipped. Unequipping a trinket does not reset adrenaline; only its generation is stopped. The maximum amount of adrenaline is defined by the equipped trinket.\n\nWhen the maximum amount of adrenaline is reached, all adrenaline is consumed and the trinket power is activated. Adrenaline can build up again without delay, even while the trinket power is active.</string>
    <string name="mob_detail_health_info">The amount of health points this creature has</string>
